From 6e46ebe072c1cdf34cc46f7d3d4727d414e378a6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Adwait Nayak <adwaitn@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 20 Aug 2025 15:24:09 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK: DP: wifi: ath12k: Add pktlog full tx support

This change takes care of below items:
1. Add sanity checks for pktlog buffer boundaries,
   buffer pointer and size to prevent crash and buffer
   overruns.
2. Refactor ath12k_pktlog_read() to avoid below call trace:

BUG: sleeping function called from invalid context at include/linux/uaccess.h:165
in_atomic(): 1, irqs_disabled(): 0, non_block: 0, pid: 19638, name: cp
preempt_count: 201, expected: 0
RCU nest depth: 0, expected: 0
CPU: 2 PID: 19638 Comm: cp Tainted: G           O       6.6.88+ #0
Hardware name: Qualcomm Technologies, Inc. IPQ9574/RDP433/AP-AL02-C4 (DT)
Call trace:
 dump_backtrace+0xd4/0xf4
 show_stack+0x14/0x1c
 dump_stack_lvl+0x44/0x58
 dump_stack+0x14/0x1c
 __might_resched+0x124/0x13c
 __might_sleep+0x60/0x6c
 __might_fault+0x18/0x24
 ath12k_erp_handle_ssr+0x268/0xe78 [ath12k]
 full_proxy_read+0x54/0x80
 vfs_read+0xac/0x21c
 ksys_read+0x74/0xec
 __arm64_sys_read+0x14/0x1c
 el0_svc_common.constprop.0+0xc8/0x120
 do_el0_svc+0x18/0x20
 el0_svc+0x18/0x40
 el0t_64_sync_handler+0x80/0x124
 el0t_64_sync+0x150/0x154

3. Update TLV subscription in case of LITE_T2H.
  Below TLVs are needed in pktlog lite tx data during critical
  issue debugging:
  HTT_PPDU_STATS_USERS_INFO,
  HTT_PPDU_STATS_USR_MPDU_ENQ_BITMAP_1024_TLV,
  HTT_PPDU_STATS_USR_COMPLTN_BA_BITMAP_1024_TLV,

  num_users and success_bytes info was missing the pktlog data.
  Subscribing HTT_PPDU_STATS_USERS_INFO TLV fixes that issue.

Signed-off-by: Adwait Nayak <adwaitn@qti.qualcomm.com>
